Statement_English: This guy must have about 3 extra chromosomes
Statement_Language: Hierdie man moet ongeveer 3 ekstra chromosome hê
Reply:
Die stelling "Hierdie man moet ongeveer 3 ekstra chromosome hê" is 'n hiperbool en word waarskynlik gebruik om 'n punt te maak of om humoristies te wees. In werklikheid is dit nie moontlik vir 'n mens om 3 ekstra chromosome te hê en steeds lewendig te wees nie. 

Menslike selle het normaalweg 46 chromosome, verdeel in 23 pare. Genetiese afwykings soos Down-sindroom, wat veroorsaak word deur 'n ekstra chromosoom 21, is een van die min voorbeelde waar 'n mens 'n ekstra chromosoom kan hê. Die teenwoordigheid van meer as een ekstra chromosoom is baie seldsaam en sou ernstige gesondheidsprobleme veroorsaak.

Dus, die stelling is nie wetenskaplik akkuraat nie en word waarskynlik gebruik in 'n figuurlike sin om 'n sterk uitdrukking te maak oor die persoon in kwessie.
EnglishTranslation:
The statement "This man must have about 3 extra chromosomes" is a hyperbole and is probably used to make a point or to be humorous. In reality, it is not possible for a person to have 3 extra chromosomes and still be alive. 

Human cells normally have 46 chromosomes, divided into 23 pairs. Genetic disorders such as Down syndrome, caused by an extra chromosome 21, are one of the few examples where one can have an extra chromosome. The presence of more than one extra chromosome is very rare and would cause serious health problems.

Thus, the statement is not scientifically accurate and is probably used in a figurative sense to make a strong expression on the person in issue.
